-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Admiral Group, Direct Line, Edenred
-- 
-- Thu Sep 11, 2014 02:17AM EDT
-- None



Sept 1 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Admiral Group, Direct Line and Tryg, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Admiral Group PLC <ADML.L>: Numis raises to buy from add * Direct Line <DLGD.L>: Numis cuts to hold from add * Tryg A/S <TRYG.CO>: Goldman Sachs raises to buy from neutral Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Admiral Group PLC <ADML.L>: Numis raises to buy from add * Admiral Group PLC <ADML.L>: Numis cuts price target by 90p to 1630p * Direct Line <DLGD.L>: Numis cuts to hold from add * Edenred <EDEN.PA>: Berenberg starts with sell rating; price target 17 euros * Iliad <ILD.PA>: SocGen cuts target price to 200 euros from 237 euros; rating buy * Informa <INF.L>: Panmure re-introduces buy rating; target price 620p * Lanson BCC <LAN.PA>: Barclays cuts target price to 36 euros from 38.50 euros; equal weight